other_tests.findings: At 6 hours, blood glucose level was 48 mg/dL; at 8 hours, blood glucose level was 29 mg/dL with symptoms of weakness and fatigue.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Following administration of orange juice and dextrose, the glucose level rose to 200 mg/dL and the weakness and fatigue resolved.

other_tests.findings: Revealed a hypoechoic, homogeneous, well-defined, nearly spherical lesion (1.6 cm) in the head of the pancreas.
Cellular pattern with moderately cohesive clusters of relatively monomorphic tumor cells and approximately 2% of tumor cells stained positive for Ki-67, consistent with a grade 1 tumor.
